ccessible style, The Inequality Trap is the must-read rejoinder to the idea that fighting inequality should be our top policy priority.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCapitalism. 0aEconomics. 0aEquality. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144262494840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442624948423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442624948.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles